---
title: Caramelized Onion Organic Beef Meatloaves  with Sumac Roasted Carrots & Zucchini
description: Glaze ‘em, smother ‘em, stuff ‘em—meatloaves really can do it all. These loaves mix things up with a spoonful of creamy sauce over top, made with sweet caramelized onion, cream cheese, butter, and a pinch of parsley. On the side, sumac—a tangy Middle Eastern spice—seasons carrots and zucchini with citrusy flavor (similar to lemon zest!). Serve it all together, letting the sauce pool around the veggies, for a perfectly paired plate and yet another meatloaf miracle.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/642af2dc539d2a08cf015dc5-6e1b5500.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6526e6efca6ba9ab416310bc.pdf
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 690 kcal
  fat: 46 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 39 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 31 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 990 mg
cuisine: North America
time required: 35 minutes
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/caramelized-onion-organic-beef-meatloaves-6526e6efca6ba9ab416310bc
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and
preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces.
Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into 1-inch-thick
half-moons.

In a #medium bowl{} (use a large bowl for 4 servings), gently combine
@organic ground beef{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup},
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{3/4%tsp} (we used ¾ tsp; 1¼ tsp for 4),
and @pepper{}.

Form into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4).

> Swap in organic beef for beef.

Place meatloaves on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. TIP: Line sheet
with foil first for easier cleanup.

Toss carrots on empty side with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon},
salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets; roast meatloaves on
middle rack and carrots on top rack.)

Roast on top rack until meatloaves are cooked through and carrots are browned
and tender, ~{22-25%minutes}. TIP: Love extra-crispy veggies? Once meatloaves are
done, remove from sheet and continue roasting carrots for ~{2-3%minutes} more.

While everything roasts, halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}.
Pick @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick,
#pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini; cook, stirring, until softened and
lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes} (7-10 minutes for 4 servings). Turn off heat;
transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Add a large drizzle of oil to same pan over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook,
stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{6-9%minutes}. TIP: Lower
heat and add a splash of water if onion begins to brown too quickly.

Add @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/2%cup},
and @sugar{3/4%teaspoon} (1 1/2 tsp for 4 servings) to pan with onion; cook until
thickened, ~{1-3%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) and a pinch of
chopped parsley. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Carefully toss zucchini and carrots together with half the @sumac{1%teaspoon}
(all for 4 servings).

Divide meatloaves and carrots and zucchini between plates. Spoon caramelized
onion sauce over meatloaves; garnish with remaining chopped parsley. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160º.